<sect1 id="mesa-demos" xreflabel="Mesa-Demos-&mesa-demos-version;">
  <?dbhtml filename="mesa-demos.html"?>

  <title>Mesa-Demos-&mesa-demos-version;</title>

  <indexterm zone="mesa-demos">
    <primary sortas="a-mesa-demos">Mesa-Demos</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to Mesa-Demos</title>

    <para>
      The Mesa-Demos package provides multiple demos
      to test the installation of multiple graphics APIs and drivers for those
      APIs, such as OpenGL, EGL, Vulkan, and more.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&mesa-demos-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Additional Downloads</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Required patch:
          <ulink url="https://gitlab.archlinux.org/archlinux/packaging/packages/mesa-demos/-/raw/main/mesa-demos-system-data.patch"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">mesa-demos Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      &opengl;
      <footnote><para>
        The more support built into the OpenGL provider, like EGL, GLES, and
        others, the more demos will get built unless specified otherwise in the
        <command>meson setup</command> options.
      </para></footnote>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Recommended</bridgehead>
    <para role="recommended">
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/libpng.html">libpng</ulink>:
            Required for the <command>readtex</command> utility.
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            &gbm;:
            Required for EGL with KMS (Kernel Mode Setting).
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/glslang.html">glslang</ulink> and
            <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/vulkan-loader.html">Vulkan-Loader</ulink>:
            Required for Vulkan demos.
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/libxkbcommon.html">libxkbcommon</ulink>:
            Required for X11/Wayland demos.
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/x7lib.html">Xorg Libraries</ulink>:
            Required for X11 demos.
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <xref linkend="libdecor"/> (will be downloaded if it is not
            installed),
            <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/wayland.html">Wayland</ulink>, and
            <ulink
            url="&blfs-svn;/general/wayland-protocols.html">Wayland-Protocols</ulink>:
            Required for Wayland demos.
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/freeglut.html">Freeglut</ulink>
            (with &glu;): Recommended for X11 demos; will be
            automatically downloaded if it is not disabled or installed.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Mesa-Demos</title>

    <para>
      First apply a patch so that shaders and other necessary data get copied
      over during installation:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -Np1 -i ../mesa-demos-system-data.patch</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install Mesa-Demos by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

meson setup --prefix=/usr --buildtype=release .. &amp;&amp;
ninja</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now do a destdir installation and rename some binaries that conflict with
      other packages outside of the LFS books:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>DESTDIR=$PWD/DESTDIR ninja install &amp;&amp;
for bin in {identity,linktest,poly}; do
  mv -v DESTDIR/usr/bin/{$bin,mesa-$bin}
done</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      If you only want the utilities, or important demos built by this package,
      install just them as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>mesa_utils=(
  eglgears_wayland
  eglgears_x11
  eglinfo
  eglkms
  egltri_wayland
  egltri_x11
  es1_info
  es2_info
  es2gears_wayland
  es2gears_x11
  es2tri
  gears
  glxgears
  glxinfo
  peglgears
  tri
  vkgears
  xeglgears
)
for util in ${mesa_utils[@]}; do
  install -vDm755 DESTDIR/usr/bin/$util -t /usr/bin/
done
cp -vR DESTDIR/usr/share/* /usr/share</userinput></screen>

    <note><para>
      You may get multiple errors of a given utility not being able to be
      installed. This is normal as you likely won't have every utility built.
      A number of them should still get installed, however.
    </para></note>

    <para>
      If you wish to install every demo (less important binaries built in this
      package), then run the following command as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>cp -vR DESTDIR/usr/* /usr</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Command Explanations</title>

    &meson-buildtype-release;

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="content">
    <title>Contents</title>

    <note><para>
      Not every demo will be shown here. Please check all the built binaries in
      <filename class="directory">$DESTDIR/usr/bin</filename> as it will
      greatly vary depending on what you have installed, how you built OpenGL,
      etc.
    </para></note>

    <segmentedlist>
      <segtitle>Installed Utilities</segtitle>
      <segtitle>Installed Libraries</segtitle>
      <segtitle>Installed Directories</segtitle>

      <seglistitem>
        <seg>
          eglgears_wayland,
          eglgears_x11,
          eglinfo,
          eglkms,
          egltri_wayland,
          egltri_x11,
          es1_info,
          es2_info,
          es2gears_wayland,
          es2gears_x11,
          es2tri,
          gears,
          glxgears,
          glxinfo,
          peglgears,
          tri,
          vkgears, and
          xeglgears
        </seg>
        <seg>
          None
        </seg>
        <seg>
          /usr/share/mesa-demos
        </seg>
      </seglistitem>
    </segmentedlist>

